
## âœ… PART 2: NCPA (Nagios Cross Platform Agent) with Nagios

---

### ğŸ’» Step 1: Install NCPA on Windows

1. Download from: [https://www.nagios.org/ncpa/](https://www.nagios.org/ncpa/)
2. Install and set a secure token.
3. Default port: `5693`

ğŸ”‘ Save your token! (used in checks)

---

### ğŸ’¡ Step 2: On Nagios Machine

#### ğŸ”¸ a. Download NCPA plugin

```bash
cd /usr/lib/nagios/plugins
sudo wget https://assets.nagios.com/downloads/ncpa/check_ncpa.py
sudo chmod +x check_ncpa.py
```

#### ğŸ”¸ b. Update Python interpreter (if needed)

Open the file:

```bash
sudo nano check_ncpa.py
```

Change first line:

```python
#!/usr/bin/env python3
```

---

### ğŸ› ï¸ Step 3: Define NCPA command in Nagios

Edit:

```bash
sudo nano /usr/local/nagios/etc/objects/commands.cfg
```

Add:

```cfg
define command {
    command_name    check_ncpa
    command_line    $USER1$/check_ncpa.py -H $HOSTADDRESS$ $ARG1$
}
```

---

### ğŸ§± Step 4: Enable `cfg_dir` in `nagios.cfg`

Edit:

```bash
sudo nano /usr/local/nagios/etc/nagios.cfg
```

Uncomment or add:

```cfg
cfg_dir=/usr/local/nagios/etc/servers
```

---

### ğŸ“ Step 5: Create `servers/` directory & Windows host config

```bash
sudo mkdir /usr/local/nagios/etc/servers
sudo nano /usr/local/nagios/etc/servers/win10-1.cfg
```

Paste the following:

```cfg
define host {
    use                     windows-server
    host_name               win10-1
    alias                   Windows 10 Sys 1
    address                 <Windows-IP>
    max_check_attempts      5
}

define service {
    use                     generic-service
    host_name               win10-1
    service_description     NCPA version check
    check_command           check_ncpa!-t 'your_token' -P 5693 -M system/agent_version
}

define service {
    use                     generic-service
    host_name               win10-1
    service_description     CPU average
    check_command           check_ncpa!-t 'your_token' -P 5693 -M cpu/percent -w 20 -c 40 -q 'aggregate=avg'
}
```

Replace:

* `<Windows-IP>` with actual IP of your Windows machine
* `'your_token'` with the actual NCPA token

---

### ğŸ›‘ Step 6: Comment default Windows template (optional fix)

Edit:

```bash
sudo nano /usr/local/nagios/etc/objects/templates.cfg
```

Comment:

```cfg
# cfg_file=/usr/local/nagios/etc/objects/windows.cfg
```

---

### ğŸ”„ Step 7: Restart Nagios

```bash
sudo systemctl restart nagios
```

---

## âœ… Final Check

* Access Nagios Web UI â†’ see `win10-1` host and NCPA checks
* Go to `http://<nginx-ip>` to verify NGINX reverse proxy

